Date: Fri, 7 Feb 2025 16:39:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 114/124] Merged PR 11704481: Resolve a build error

VTL0: Minor fix

heki_store_blacklist_raw_hashes() is defined as an init.text
function. But it is called by a non init.text function. This causes
a build warning. This is wrong also because the memory for init
functions and data are freed at the end of kernel boot. For now,
remove the __init attribute for the function.

Signed-off-by: Madhavan T. Venkataraman <madvenka@linux.microsoft.com>

----
